UserComments.Comment: 13A socket has been repaired and I am now charging on it. An Outlander is charging on the 7Kw side.
13A side still isn't working after 8 weeks and being reported 3 times. However 7Kw side is fine.
13a side is still broken but 7Kw side is charging an i3.
13A side flap would open but could not insert my plug more than half way. I have informed Chargemaster.
Mercedes B and an i3 charging. This site is getting popular so getting a charge is difficult.

7Kw side is available.
Cones are back out :-)

CheckinStatusType.Title: Charging Spot In Use (Other EV Parked)

UserComments.Comment: Staff do their best to stop post being ICE'D but with only one post and a popular choice it's generally a car charging that stops you getting the charge.
Simon you are not the only one I have seen parking creatively to get a charge here. You were lucky it was closed as with only one post you can't guarantee a charge.

Park and ride was closed (New Year's Day), but with some creative parking and a long cable managed to get enough charge to continue with my journey.  Source East charge point,  worked with Source London card.
Single charge point is not enough lots of Leaf's Audi, Outlander's  and i3's in the car park.
Leaf and Audi Etron charging more points required as all of Chelmsford's  points in use. Good news but time for expansion.

CheckinStatusType.Title: Charging Spot In Use (Other EV Parked)

UserComments.Comment: Another Gunmetal Leaf charging next to mine so hopefully Source East will soon put in an additional charger.
Two cars charging today one Leaf the other an Outlander so we could do with more points.
Both bays were clear and accessible and according to the site staff regularly used. Today the points were saying that they were OK.

MediaItems.Comment: A bitter sweet moment as a lovely Tesla S is stopping my Zoe from charging as it doesn't have a Granny charger.
